        <div xml:id="OTP32056009">
        <fw type="pageNum">Letter from Simon M. Preston to General N. A. M. Dudley; July 20, 1868</fw>
          <p corresp='TTP32056009P0' xml:id='OTP32056009P0'><rs ref='#S63019'>Natchez</rs> Miss. July 20 1868
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32056009P1' xml:id='OTP32056009P1'>General. <rs ref='#S32022573'>Dudly</rs><lb/>
Comdg. Natchez Miss
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32056009P2' xml:id='OTP32056009P2'>Sir
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32056009P3' xml:id='OTP32056009P3'>The Bearer is this <rs ref='#S32022574'>Israel Etta</rs>, a resident of <rs ref='#S82506'>Washington</rs> this State. at whose house some <rs ref='#S92353'>disturbances against the Peace</rs> of the Citizens were Committed on Saturday Night last. Israel wishes to state what occurred. He was a Corporal in my <rs ref='#S25006301'>Regiment</rs> and was Considered a very reliable soldier—
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32056009P4' xml:id='OTP32056009P4'>Very Respectfully<lb/>
Your obt serv't
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32056009P5' xml:id='OTP32056009P5'><rs ref='#S32022575'>S, M, Preston</rs>—
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32056009P6' xml:id='OTP32056009P6'>I full<sub>y</sub> concure in the above, having known the man for the last 3 yers.
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32056009P7' xml:id='OTP32056009P7'>Fraternally Yours
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32056009P8' xml:id='OTP32056009P8'><rs ref='#S32022576'>Geo, Sr, C, Hussey</rs>
</p>


        </div>
  </body>
